Daiwa’s Biggest Shareholder Harris Increases Stake to 13.4%

-- B y   T a k a h i k o   H y u g a
-- 
2011-08-05T07:19:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/daiwa-s-biggest-shareholder-harris-increases-stake-to-13-4-1-.html
Daiwa Securities Group Inc. (8601) ’s biggest
shareholder Harris Associates LP increased its stake in  Japan ’s
second-largest brokerage to 13.44 percent from 12.44 percent.  The Chicago-based investment fund held 235.2 million shares
as of Aug. 2, it said in a filing to Japan’s Finance Ministry
today. Harris, which has been adding Daiwa shares since 2007,
raised its holdings four times this year, ministry filings show.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Takahiko Hyuga in Tokyo at 
